                "invention-title": [
                    "Method for preparing azobenzene through reduction coupling of electrocatalytic nitrobenzene",
                    "一种电催化硝基苯还原偶联制备偶氮苯的方法"
                ]
            },
            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The invention discloses a method for preparing azobenzene by electro-catalysis nitrobenzene reduction coupling, which comprises the following steps: under an alkaline medium condition, taking electric energy as a driving force of reaction, water as an active hydrogen source, nitrobenzene as a synthesis raw material and mesoporous palladium-sulfur nanoparticles as a catalyst of reaction, and adopting a three-electrode system to synthesize azobenzene. Nitrobenzene is subjected to electrocatalytic reduction and coupling in an electrolyte under different voltages to generate azobenzene. The adopted catalyst shows good catalytic activity, selectivity and stability in nitrobenzene electrocatalytic reduction coupling reaction, the conversion rate of nitrobenzene reaches 95.4%, the selectivity of the product azobenzene reaches 93.4%, and in six circular reactions, the conversion rate of reactants and the selectivity of the product are not obviously reduced. According to the present invention, the renewable electric energy is adopted as the driving force, the clean and easily available water is adopted as the hydrogen source, the reaction performance is excellent, the characteristics of greenness, cleanliness and high efficiency are provided, and the new strategy is provided for the azobenzene synthesis."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本发明公开了一种电催化硝基苯还原偶联制备偶氮苯的方法，该方法在碱性介质条件下，以电能作为反应的驱动力，水作为活性氢来源，硝基苯作为合成原料，介孔钯硫纳米颗粒作为反应的催化剂，采用三电极体系，在电解液中不同电压下电催化还原硝基苯偶联生成偶氮苯。本发明采用的催化剂在硝基苯电催化还原偶联的反应中表现出良好的催化活性、选择性以及稳定性，其中硝基苯的转化率达到95.4％，产物偶氮苯的选择性达93.4％，在六个循环反应中，反应物的转化率与产物选择性没有明显的下降。本发明利用可再生的电能为驱动力，清洁易得的水作为氢源，反应性能优异，具有绿色清洁、高效的特征，为偶氮苯的合成提供了一种新策略。"
                }
            ]
